📊 Customer Segmentation: Cluster Analysis (Part 3)

This project is a continuation of K-Means Clustering (Part 2), where we perform cluster-level analysis to interpret the segments and extract actionable business insights.

The objective is to move beyond clustering and understand the true value and behavior of each customer segment.

🔧 Tools & Technologies Used
Python
Pandas
Matplotlib
Seaborn
Jupyter Notebook
📁 Dataset
Online Retail Dataset (same dataset used in Part 1 & Part 2)
⚙️ Methodology
1️⃣ Cluster Mapping

Merged cluster labels with the original dataset to associate each transaction with a customer segment.

2️⃣ Revenue Analysis

Calculated total revenue generated by each cluster to identify high-performing segments.

3️⃣ Customer Distribution

Analyzed the number of unique customers in each cluster to understand segment size.

4️⃣ Spending Behavior

Evaluated average spending patterns across clusters to compare customer value.

5️⃣ Segment Comparison

Compared clusters based on:

Revenue contribution
Customer count
Average spending
📊 Visualization
Bar Chart → Revenue by Cluster
Pie Chart → Customer distribution by Cluster
Box Plot → Spending distribution across clusters
💡 Key Insights
A small cluster of high-value customers contributes the largest share of total revenue, despite having fewer customers
Mid-value customers represent a strong opportunity for growth through targeted marketing and upselling
Low-value customers form a large portion of the customer base but contribute less revenue
Clear differences in spending patterns across clusters validate the effectiveness of K-Means segmentation
Customer distribution is uneven, highlighting the importance of focused business strategies for each segment
🚀 Business Impact

Cluster analysis enables:

🎯 Targeted marketing strategies for each customer segment
💎 Improved retention of high-value customers
📈 Growth opportunities through mid-value customer conversion
📣 Engagement strategies for low-value customers
📊 Better decision-making using segment-level insights
